Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.05,0:02:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's an audio commentary.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.84,0:02:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Sato. I worked on the set\Nand the script. I'll be your host today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.58,0:02:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We have two guests today. Let me\Nintroduce them one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.35,0:02:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The first person is... please go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.08,0:02:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, I'm Kouichi Yamadera,\Nvoice of Spike.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.19,0:02:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to be here. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.62,0:02:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, our second guest...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.86,0:02:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see... I'm... Jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.93,0:02:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That sure took you a while!\NYou had to think hard to remember?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.80,0:02:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- How is that possible?!\N- Unbelievable! You're confusing us!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.14,0:02:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. I'm Unsho Ishizuka,\Nvoice of Jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.07,0:02:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,At least he remembered his own name.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.44,0:02:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- At least!\N- He couldn't remember the name "Jet".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.01,0:03:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He was just hemming and hawing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.91,0:03:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't sure if I should say his\Nfull name. You know... like... Black Jet?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.38,0:03:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- Or Jet Black?\N- Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.92,0:03:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That's pretty bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.92,0:03:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, let's try Spike's full name.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.32,0:03:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys are mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.19,0:03:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll give you a little test.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.69,0:03:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- His last name's Spiegel, isn't it?\N- Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.73,0:03:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, it's already started.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.56,0:03:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the first line of the series.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.76,0:03:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's this thing called? Commen...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.27,0:03:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- Audio commentary.\N- I've been looking forward to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.97,0:03:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- Really?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.60,0:03:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- You haven't done it before?\N- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.34,0:03:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This is really my first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.07,0:03:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's cool you can watch it and hear us.\N- Yeah. I love that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.58,0:03:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But you have to wonder how many\Npeople will actually switch the tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.21,0:03:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... really.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.88,0:03:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is the first episode and\Nthe first time these characters speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.42,0:03:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It begins with the Chinese dish,\N"Julienned beef and bell peppers."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.36,0:03:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.76,0:03:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I just remember the julienned beef\Nand bell pepper Chinese dish.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.96,0:03:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But I wasn't sure\Nwhat the setting was.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.53,0:03:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'm watching it,\NI understand better.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.63,0:03:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then we were still\Nkind of fumbling our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.00,0:03:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Those characters weren't\Nfinalized yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.20,0:03:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.90,0:04:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's right.\N- It was only the first episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.74,0:04:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The picture was still messy, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.94,0:04:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops, can I say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.04,0:04:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically, the picture wasn't\Nthis clear back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.55,0:04:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jet was scary-looking\Nlike this from the get-go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.09,0:04:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he was kinda cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.12,0:04:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's what I was aiming for.\N- Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.99,0:04:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going a little too far...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.89,0:04:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I was aiming for cutesy idol-ish style.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.43,0:04:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean like Akira Ishida?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.96,0:04:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. I was trying to imitate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.96,0:04:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hear it.\NWhy don't you do Jet in his voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.43,0:04:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's Akira Ishida's version of Jet.\NTake it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.40,0:04:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Julienned beef...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.31,0:04:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,At least you gave it a try.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.61,0:04:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I also wasn't sure how to\Ncharacterize Spike.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.25,0:04:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,As I recall, wasn't he the first\Nmain character you ever dubbed?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.58,0:04:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- In a TV series? Yes.\N- Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.75,0:04:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.45,0:04:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And I didn't do much after that, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.26,0:04:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.26,0:04:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably because you're too great\Nto be asked to do serialized shows.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.33,0:04:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Scenes like these were mind-boggling.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.60,0:05:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't grasp the concept just by\Nlistening to the explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.27,0:05:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I was clueless. Even when they described\Nmy character, I didn't quite get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.37,0:05:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But, in substance, it's more of a\Nhuman drama than a SF story.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.31,0:05:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. This episode in particular...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.98,0:05:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,featured the friendship between\Nthese two guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.91,0:05:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's a brilliant as SF with a nice\Nbalance of CG and anime and all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.88,0:05:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost amateur-like. I don't know\Nif I can call it that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.66,0:05:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It was unprecedented for\Na TV series.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.46,0:05:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What about this whistling?\NDidn't you do it yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.86,0:05:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, I did.\N- It's coming back to you, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.89,0:05:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I remember it well, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.30,0:05:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I'd do it myself. They told me\Nthey needed sort of a listless song.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.77,0:05:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just did it on the fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.30,0:05:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, it was ad-libbed?\N- It sure was.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.84,0:05:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? Ad-libbed?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.51,0:05:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I was intimidated because Yoko Kanno,\Nthe genius, was doing the music, ya' know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.45,0:05:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That goes to show you how clueless\NI was back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.61,0:05:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He came up with a very listless song.\NI thought he was a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.39,0:05:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm flattered.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.72,0:05:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I need to praise you, Unsho-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.12,0:06:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you don't have to. I'm serious.\NThat's really how I felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.06,0:06:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What they requested was\Nkind of complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.09,0:06:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.76,0:06:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It had to sound kinda listless,\Nbut it had to sound cool in a way, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.77,0:06:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If I remember correctly,\Nthat's what they asked for.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.47,0:06:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember anything but\Nsomething trivial like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.34,0:06:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,At that point, Unsho-san and I were\Nthe only regular characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.78,0:06:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's right.\N- Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.28,0:06:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just two of us and\Nsome incidental guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.35,0:06:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Later on, those old guys joined us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.78,0:06:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right. They were there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.75,0:06:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They appeared very frequently. They\Nwere there till the end of the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.05,0:06:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, those three old guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.56,0:06:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They were main incidentals.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.99,0:06:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Here they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.63,0:06:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what it was, but they\Nsomehow managed to show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.56,0:06:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I always wondered\Nhow they moved around.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.96,0:06:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- They showed up everywhere.\N- They sure did.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.50,0:06:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember their names?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.87,0:06:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Taro, Jiro... Saburo...\NWasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.71,0:06:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- Carlos... Antonio, Carlos and Jobin.\N- That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.41,0:06:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually that's the name of\Na bossa nova composer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.65,0:06:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really. I didn't know.\NI've just found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.95,0:07:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean one person?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.22,0:07:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one person by the name of\NAntonio Carlos Jobin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.09,0:07:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point their names weren't\Nin the script yet. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.33,0:07:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.89,0:07:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like Old Man 1, Old Man 2...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.13,0:07:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But maybe Nabeshin-san already had\Nthat name in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.50,0:07:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And these two... they were the guests\Nin the first episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.44,0:07:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,She's got big boobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.30,0:07:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I was stunned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.91,0:07:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You're too much... stunned by\Nbig boobs in an anime?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.21,0:07:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate it was awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.18,0:07:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This setup was awesome, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.65,0:07:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I can say this because\Nit wasn't aired on a certain TV station...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.22,0:07:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.19,0:07:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This was completely cut, and it didn't\Nreally get going until the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.72,0:07:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, at first, it almost looked like\NEin the dog was the main character.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.09,0:07:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought this was the best plot ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.96,0:07:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,When I watched Episode 1, it looked\Ntoo mature for the early evening slot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.63,0:07:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, because the first episode was\Nadvertised on a late night show.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.64,0:07:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Boobs!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.17,0:07:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Boobs and Carlos Jobin, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.61,0:07:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it was advertised on TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.48,0:08:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it was talked about\Nduring a live TV talk show.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.04,0:08:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. There was a segment dedicated\Nto the show airing later that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.21,0:08:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This particular scene would have\Nnever been shown in that segment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.95,0:08:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a little too hairy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.82,0:08:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That was an eye drop, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.06,0:08:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, an eye drop caused that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.06,0:08:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually an eye drop reduces red-eye,\Nbut this one caused it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.79,0:08:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,These images were mind-boggling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.63,0:08:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.13,0:08:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Only people who've experienced it\Nwould know what it's like.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.00,0:08:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on. That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.10,0:08:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey, that's sort of a scary thought.\N- Really. That's dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.14,0:08:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Unsho-san's getting dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.24,0:08:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You know... you're being zeroed in on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.44,0:08:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean? What did I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.68,0:08:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone tipped you off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.98,0:08:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the show was full of\Nelements like that... like tip-offs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.72,0:08:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end I was tipped off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.05,0:08:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I just have to wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.72,0:08:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,While making Episode 1, did the staff\Nwant to make it sensational?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.99,0:08:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,At first the staff didn't know\Nwhat the director was shooting for.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.73,0:08:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We sort of figured it out\Nas we created the first 5 to 6 episodes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.47,0:09:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- This is very different from others.\N- I've never seen anything like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.71,0:09:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Particularly... when you think about\Nthe fact that this is a TV series.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.21,0:09:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.44,0:09:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder how the budget was managed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.48,0:09:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.45,0:09:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This is impossible for a TV series.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.35,0:09:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, it was reckless.\N- But Unsho-san was impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.35,0:09:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.12,0:09:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- It was a certain group of people.\N- No, it's not that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.26,0:09:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain group of people...\NWe'll just leave it at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.29,0:09:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy... he was mysterious.\NI didn't know what he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.00,0:09:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- A Prophet.\N- Yeah. He appeared a couple of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.10,0:09:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. He was in a movie, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.54,0:09:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He shows up in important scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.47,0:09:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- Right. Bull.\N- He's called Bull.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.34,0:09:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He's Ms. Nobumoto's creation.\NShe likes to add characters like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.45,0:09:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. You see someone like him\Nin every episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.72,0:09:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- Unsho-san really likes Ms. Nobumoto.\N- Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.42,0:09:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the other way round. She likes me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.59,0:09:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.89,0:10:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been rumored lately that\Nmy figure has changed a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.63,0:10:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this conversation's going to be\Nmade public, so let's be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.00,0:10:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it could come back\Nto bite you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.00,0:10:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It they cut this part out, there'll be\Na blank spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.34,0:10:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I just said that my figure changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.61,0:10:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I never mentioned how it changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.45,0:10:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess this guy is saying\Nsomething important. I wasn't listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.45,0:10:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This is when he's mentioning Julia.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.95,0:10:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The beginning of the first episode\Nis suggestive but chaotic as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.63,0:10:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You never got any explanation\Nwhen you first started out?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.63,0:10:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- No.\N- There was none.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.40,0:10:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was more like,\N"OK. Let's get started."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.73,0:10:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,After that first scene, Jet and Spike\Nshow up as partners out of the blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.11,0:10:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that was crazy and funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.68,0:10:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not that close as partners.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.88,0:10:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The most unlikely guys paired up\Nand that was kinda interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.98,0:10:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,One is a former cop and the other is\Nformer Mafia.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.09,0:10:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, yeah, I used to be a cop.\N- That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.25,0:10:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- So things are coming back to you.\N- Yeah, finally.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.29,0:11:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I used to be a truck driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.16,0:11:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that would be\NTomie Kataoka's character.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.36,0:11:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, yeah.\N- There was something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.70,0:11:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a different scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.74,0:11:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He's using this like a bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.74,0:11:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so cool. All the machines in here\Nare just awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.81,0:11:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He's always hungry, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.48,0:11:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.88,0:11:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,At first I thought there would be\Nmore funny scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.05,0:11:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- This whistling...\N- It was also ad-libbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.69,0:11:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference between serious and\Nfunny scenes are extreme in the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.63,0:11:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Also no particular effort is\Nmade to make the audience laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.30,0:11:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's true.\N- Unsho-san said very few gags.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.10,0:11:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Gags... I hardly said any.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.83,0:11:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- In real life you like gags, right?\N- Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.54,0:11:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm a serious type.\N- You, on the other hand, like puns.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.94,0:11:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no. At least not like Mr. Hirokawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.98,0:11:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not too crazy about puns.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.55,0:12:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a scene in a restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.22,0:12:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How long has it been?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.72,0:12:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- Six or seven?\N- Long, long time ago, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.79,0:12:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't wanna say something\Nto be frowned upon, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.56,0:12:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I was gonna make him say\Nsomething like "because it smells bad..."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.26,0:12:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was told not to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.03,0:12:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe "It stinks" or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.64,0:12:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- No. That wouldn't work.\N- It's not funny when you try too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.37,0:12:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- The first half has ended?!\N- Yep. It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.44,0:12:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so dense.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.65,0:12:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, it's so "stylish." Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.18,0:12:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.42,0:12:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no. How pathetic!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.42,0:12:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- Why?\N- Right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.72,0:12:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- A woman meets a man.\N- You almost think it's a gag.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.99,0:12:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,When I spit it out,\NI use a little trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.00,0:12:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I say the first part of "Excuse me"\Nwith my mouth full.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.00,0:12:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.57,0:12:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't sure if I could do a gag like\NLupin or City Hunter would.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.91,0:13:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I ad-lib something\Noff-camera after this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.28,0:13:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Right here. Right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.51,0:13:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I think about it, Spike shouldn't\Nhave said anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.65,0:13:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd only think that after 26 episodes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.29,0:13:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,When we were recording Episode 1,\Nwe had no clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.92,0:13:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Using a wallet as an excuse, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.99,0:13:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In all 26 episodes that was the only\Ntime I ad-libbed a stupid gag like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.89,0:13:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, really.\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.90,0:13:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't the director frowning?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.70,0:13:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the director just couldn't\Nsay no back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.70,0:13:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He couldn't tell me to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.24,0:13:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Kobayashi was probably thinking\N"Whatever..."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.54,0:13:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He probably thought the show was\Nlike that to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.91,0:13:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you establish your character\Nby exploring little by little?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.11,0:13:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In my case... I'm not sure\Nif I could say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.28,0:13:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,At the audition I asked them\Nhow they wanted me to act.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.29,0:13:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They asked me to be myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.42,0:13:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,"Myself?" I asked, and they said\Nthey wanted me the way I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.13,0:13:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I just did it the way\NI naturally would.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.50,0:13:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, they said, "Fine."\NI never changed anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.03,0:13:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there was absolutely\Nno performance notes, Unsho-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.07,0:14:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's not that. It's just\Nthat's all I can do and nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.97,0:14:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no different than talking about\Ngolf with people at the studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.44,0:14:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can use the same tone of voice\Nwhen performing, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.68,0:14:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.54,0:14:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to work harder than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.25,0:14:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. It was different in Spike's case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.38,0:14:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But, in the end,\NI wasn't really thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.12,0:14:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically... he had to sound calm,\Naloof and natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.29,0:14:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I was always told not to try too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.56,0:14:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.39,0:14:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you still try too hard?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.03,0:14:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,As a voice actor I couldn't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.50,0:14:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I worked with Mr. Watanabe on\Nanother show before this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.87,0:14:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't remember that though...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.01,0:14:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like, "Have we met before?"\N"I directed the previous show."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.78,0:14:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,"Ah, you're the director?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.08,0:14:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,"How do you do? Happy to meet you."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.18,0:14:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,"Well, we already met on the show\Nbefore this."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.45,0:14:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"What? What did you do?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.99,0:14:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- "I was the director."\N- It wasn't like he was just observing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.49,0:14:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was thinking... was he there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.43,0:14:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- No matter.\N- He WAS the director!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.56,0:15:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm glad I met him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.03,0:15:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I worked on anime a little before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.70,0:15:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But this was the first time I was asked\Nto talk naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.24,0:15:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It was really comfortable for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.41,0:15:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I would say it was even more natural\Nthan dubbing foreign movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.95,0:15:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Yes. Yes. I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.05,0:15:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like doing a live action movie\Nand they just took the voices.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.89,0:15:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It was really easy for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.76,0:15:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I should be\Nsaying it was easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.66,0:15:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Today we wouldn't be able to create\Nmain characters who smoke so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.97,0:15:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah. Things have certainly changed.\N- Good point.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.47,0:15:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You're absolutely right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.24,0:15:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Also each prop was very elaborate.\NThe lighter we saw earlier was cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.41,0:15:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.78,0:15:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- They sound young.\N- Do you think you sound young?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.95,0:15:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.55,0:15:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.79,0:15:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you already playing\NProfessor Oak back then?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.42,0:16:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.66,0:16:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I might have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.89,0:16:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It was about the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.73,0:16:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you doing "Good Morning Studios?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.53,0:16:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- Let's see...\N- You advertised this show in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.00,0:16:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, yeah.\N- I must have been already doing it then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.60,0:16:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,"Good Morning Studios" has been\Non the air for 8 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.40,0:16:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- I might have started it midway...\N- How old is this first episode?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.41,0:16:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- Six or...\N- You were going full swing back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.61,0:16:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,No... after we got started...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.31,0:16:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember saying I couldn't continue\Nafter the fall because...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.48,0:16:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'll be in the early morning show.\N- Oh, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.32,0:16:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was after we had recorded\Ntwo or three episodes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.99,0:16:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It was smack in the\Nmiddle of transition.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.59,0:16:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- It pretty much overlaps then.\N- It must've been seven years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.29,0:16:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that sounds right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.60,0:16:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm positive it was\Naround the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.30,0:16:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, a few episodes were done first.\N- Right. Then you went on air.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.44,0:16:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You went on the morning show\Nafter some episodes had been recorded.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.77,0:16:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You tried to advertise the show\Nbut you were still unclear about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.21,0:16:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So you probably gave up\Nand tried to quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.78,0:16:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we were always talking about\Ngoing out for drinks in Shibuya.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.45,0:17:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we recorded in May or June.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.05,0:17:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we recorded a few each month.\NWe did it sporadically.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.79,0:17:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The production schedule was relaxed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.72,0:17:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. We recorded over a long time.\NThere was no on-air schedule at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.23,0:17:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- They didn't know when it was gonna air.\N- That's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.03,0:17:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And as soon as the schedule was set,\Nthe first episode was cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.76,0:17:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's right!\N- It didn't see the light of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.00,0:17:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- When did Aoi start to appear?\N- In Episode 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.34,0:17:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, when he auditioned,\Nhe was a 9th or 10th grader?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.04,0:17:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking about that earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.64,0:17:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- When he auditioned, he was 15 or so.\N- But now he's 23.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.61,0:17:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He's old enough to get married.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.68,0:17:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He's old enough to be a father.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.95,0:17:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute! Don't go too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.48,0:17:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Unsho-san has five grandchildren, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.25,0:17:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, no way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.59,0:17:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no children or grandchildren.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.46,0:17:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You might have one somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.36,0:17:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- There might be a posthumous child.\N- Well, grandpa is working hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.96,0:17:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on. That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.10,0:17:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should talk more about\Nthe show, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.50,0:17:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Something about the story?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.17,0:17:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.71,0:18:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Right here he looks like a real\Nmean character with that sombrero.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.48,0:18:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The action scene right after this was\Nbreathtakingly cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.68,0:18:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It was almost like Kung Fu.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.42,0:18:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It reminds you of good ol' Bruce Lee.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.42,0:18:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The moves were amazing, though.\NI couldn't see it while recording.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.49,0:18:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. You just saw the line art.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.26,0:18:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Which episode did we see when\Nit was finished? We all applauded.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.27,0:18:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, we watched this together.\N- Was it this episode?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.00,0:18:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- We watched this when it was done.\N- Oh, was it the first episode?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.74,0:18:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure we watched Episode 1 together\Nwhen it was completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.47,0:18:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I was like, "I'm in such a great show?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.94,0:18:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- It was so much fun.\N- Yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.81,0:18:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- The music was awesome, too.\N- Right. Music added so much to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.92,0:18:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I was really impressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.72,0:18:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Even after so many years we can\Nstill enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.39,0:18:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm positive this will last a lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.96,0:18:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.23,0:18:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- The camera work is amazing...\N- The fact I was part of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.30,0:18:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,almost miraculous to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.07,0:19:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because this happened to be\Nmy debut.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.87,0:19:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. I was very surprised\Nto hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.97,0:19:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you had done a lot more\Nwork before this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.14,0:19:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,My workload increased after this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.41,0:19:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We owe our careers to everyone involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.68,0:19:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.88,0:19:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's kinda goofy.\N- What are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.15,0:19:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What we said was, this was maybe\NMr. Sato's debut work, but thanks to...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.66,0:19:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,all the other creative staff, it became\Na huge hit and we all benefited from it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.19,0:19:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe you spaced out\Non us!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.40,0:19:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Later on, I worked on other projects\Nwith people I met on this show.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.17,0:19:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.83,0:19:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, we did "Wolf's Rain"\Ntogether, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.17,0:19:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.67,0:19:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. It was also written\Nby Ms. Nobumoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.81,0:19:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She wrote it with me in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.55,0:19:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why she though I'd be\Nperfect as an alcoholic character.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.75,0:19:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It was quite a character.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.29,0:19:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We also worked together\Non "Stand Alone Complex".
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.12,0:19:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.\N"Stand Alone Complex"...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.49,0:19:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, once again, we worked together\Nin "Samurai Champloo"...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.99,0:19:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Watanabe directed that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.93,0:20:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- I see.\N- This was the beginning of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.10,0:20:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What a history...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.30,0:20:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the show was full of\Nbattles and fights and...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.67,0:20:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,everything was condensed\Nin one episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.71,0:20:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just flawless.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.91,0:20:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It might not have been suitable\Nfor the young morning show audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.41,0:20:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. It might have been too much\Nfor children.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.58,0:20:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Every segment is so cool and awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.52,0:20:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never seen anything this cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.82,0:20:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,In a way, a lot of non-anime fans\Nbecame hooked because of this show.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.09,0:20:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That kept the show alive\Nfor a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.93,0:20:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true for the people I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.36,0:20:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The designer who designed the clothes\NI'm wearing today got hooked...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.63,0:20:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and... so did some musicians.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.14,0:20:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, many of them...\N- Really.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.24,0:20:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The other day I was invited to go see\NMr. Children's live concert...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.71,0:20:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,James and Mr. Nakagawa are both\Nhuge fans of Cowboy Bebop.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.55,0:20:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When I talked to them after the concert,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.59,0:20:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,they said they had already placed\Nan order for the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.25,0:20:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You know... this box...\Nthe special edition of DVDs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.56,0:21:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's amazing.\N- Some people don't even know about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.59,0:21:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Unsho-san, do you even know\Nwhy we're recording this today?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.26,0:21:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This will be the bonus material\Nfor the DVDs in the special box.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.00,0:21:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you think this was for?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.33,0:21:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought maybe they were\Nre-mastering the DVD or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.34,0:21:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- You know, something like that.\N- At least you knew about the DVDs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.54,0:21:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of. I guess I was half right,\Nbut completely out of touch...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.88,0:21:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A special box version will be released.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.01,0:21:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, this is close to the ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.85,0:21:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This was such a cool scene.\NSpike was desperately trying to...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.12,0:21:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,She said "Adios!" How cool is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.59,0:21:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.29,0:21:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just too cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.16,0:21:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,She blew up and scattered like a flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.60,0:21:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at this! It's too much!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.80,0:21:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,After this show aired...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.60,0:21:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized a lot of people\Nfrom our industry watched it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.64,0:21:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I was asked to narrate some clips\Nfor a news show and I asked why.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.51,0:21:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They decided after watching\NCowboy Bebop.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.15,0:21:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,WHAT?!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.18,0:22:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- I was asked to do it just like Bebop.\N- For a news show?! It's serious stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.62,0:22:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone decided on the narrator\Nbecause he watched this show?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.16,0:22:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So I did a series of Iraq War segments\Nin the same style as Jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.76,0:22:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Just like that?\N- Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.76,0:22:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.03,0:22:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe some kickback is due...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.07,0:22:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know... part of your guarantee...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.97,0:22:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this was a cool shot, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.64,0:22:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It means the news show staff was\Nalso watching Cowboy Bebop.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.98,0:22:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. Many news guys in their 30's\Nare watching it. They're fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.92,0:22:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,On other occasions I've been asked\Nto do things like Jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.82,0:22:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... it ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.55,0:22:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we kind of babbled away.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.03,0:22:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What? It's over?\NI wanted to talk more!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.20,0:22:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to ask both of you,\Nthough it's been so long...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.40,0:22:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to briefly share your thoughts on\Nthe show, Cowboy Bebop.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.27,0:22:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- Why don't we start with Unsho-san?\N- What? Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.41,0:23:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I watched it after a long absence,\Nbut I really think it's a great show.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.21,0:23:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The music was fantastic.\NI say this all the time, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.11,0:23:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the music and animation are\Nperfectly matched.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.18,0:23:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you hear the opening music\Nthat goes "Tah-dah-dah-dah-dah..."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.72,0:23:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you almost feel the tingles\Nrunning down your spine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.56,0:23:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It really gets you prepared\Nfor the show to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.96,0:23:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, when you hear the ending song,\Nyou're like, "Ah! What a great story!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.16,0:23:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- Even now... at the age of 53.\N- Wow, that old?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.70,0:23:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I feel really old.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.30,0:23:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Even at such an age, I really like it.\NI think it's really a great show.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.31,0:23:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to get the special box version\Nand enjoy it thoroughly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.72,0:23:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you, Spike?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.98,0:23:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see... in my case...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.15,0:23:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I was interviewed a lot and participated\Nin many panel discussions for the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.12,0:23:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It means the show received\Nso much attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.46,0:23:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I always said this at every occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.33,0:23:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I would show this first episode of\NCowboy Bebop to my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.03,0:23:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And whoever doesn't think it was\Na great show is no longer my buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.57,0:24:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say, "I don't like you anymore.\NBye!" That's all there is to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.30,0:24:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I've renewed my vows. If you\Ndon't like this, I can't be your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.51,0:24:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course everyone has his own taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.01,0:24:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- That sorta summarizes it. Bye for now.\N- Cowboy Bebop forever!

